Method Detail

onUpdate

protected abstract S onUpdate(S current)
Requires the strategy to force an update of the changed properties to the implementation. This will only be invoked if changes to properties have been made which were not visible immediately to the implementation. The current implementation is given and the updated implementation must be returned.

Parameters:
current - The current strategy implementation.
Returns:
The reference to set as the implementation, or null if a problem occurred during update. If an error occurred during update the strategy must account for that itself.

onPropertyLoad

protected abstract void onPropertyLoad(java.util.List<Property<?>> props)
Loads the properties for the strategy. This is only invoked once and must be invoked as the last line of the constructor of the strategy implementation by calling the load method.

Parameters:
props - The list to add the properties.

hasChanged

public boolean hasChanged()
Returns true if atleast one property has been changed in this strategy and it requires the strategy to update for the change to take effect. If only properties that are immediate are changed this will return false.

Specified by:
hasChanged in interface Strategy<S>
Returns:
True if a property has changed and an update is required to apply it, otherwise false.

update

public boolean update()
Applies the property changes to the strategy's implementation. If changes have been made to properties that could not change immediately this will lock the implementation, apply the changes, and unlock the implementation.

Specified by:
update in interface Strategy<S>
Returns:
True if the changes applied occurred without error or if no changes needed to made, if an error occurs false will be returned.

getStatistics

public StatGroup getStatistics()
Returns the group of statistics for the strategy. This will be a directory containing each statistic tracked by the strategy. The StatGroup is only created the first time this method is invoked. This should only be invoked if this strategy is a part of a module, if it isn't then it will create its own directory and then this Strategy should not be added to any module.

Specified by:
getStatistics in interface Strategy<S>
Returns:
The reference to the strategy's group of statistics.

setStatisticsParent

public void setStatisticsParent(StatGroup parent)
Sets the parent group of this strategy's statistics. This will have no affect to this modules statistics if the getStatistics() method has already been invoked. If this isn't given the parent of the module is assumed to be root (the current working directory). This method is also automatically called when this strategy is added to a module.

Specified by:
setStatisticsParent in interface Strategy<S>
Parameters:
parent - The parent of this strategy.

getListeners

public Notifier<StrategyListener<S>> getListeners()
Returns the notifier which manages the listeners to updates in the strategy. StrategyListeners can be directly added and removed to the notifier. Avoid invoking the methods of the proxy object in the notifier since it may notify the listeners falsely when an update has not actually occurred with the strategy.

Specified by:
getListeners in interface Strategy<S>
Returns:
The reference to the StrategyListener notifier.
